# CULINEX Cursor Rules

Always read the project documentation before making code changes.

Priority documents:

- PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
- AI_RULES.md
- ROADMAP.md
- VERSION.md

Development rules:

- Never redesign the architecture.
- Never hardcode supplier-specific invoice layouts.
- Maintain backwards compatibility.
- Build one sprint at a time.
- Modify the smallest amount of code necessary.
- Keep modules independent.
- Improve universal extraction instead of template matching.

When completing work:

- Update SUMMARY.md
- Update CHANGELOG.md
- Explain modified files.
- Recommend regression tests.

The current project version is:

CULINEX Import Engine v1.0